@MathieuDuponchelle thanks for the help, I've read part of your hack, seeing that most of the work, as you said, was to get rid of QT dependancies !
This seem something doable, the difficult part, is to have a "good" API interface to have a real usable library.
@MathieuDuponchelle did you know what would be your needed interfaces ?

@Miserlou, @gwegner  here an usage  exemple : 
`./slowmoRenderer -input video ~/Videos/MVI_0233.AVI -target video cli_test.mp4 auto -slowfactor 0.5`
where `-input` is your source, `-target`is your output file and `slowfactor`is the factor you want to apply, other old `slowmoRenderer`are usable.

