> "Ability to feed the libary one buffer / frame at a time"

can you elaborate on it ?

 @petrica-celrau can you give more hint on how to reproduce/look at the problem ?
for now, the only thing I see is a change in all "monitor", not just "curve", where there is now a cache of image instead of loading them each time (less IO workload but more memory ...).
so maybe, there is a bug in the cache part (which is using qt qcache) ?
